    <text id="A7526T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Evans writes to make plans for his next visit to Sibert's home.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Miss Mollie Sibert<lb/> Miss Mollie Sibert<lb/> Mount Solon<lb/> Staunton</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-10-04">October 4th 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Miss Mollie</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your dear letter was just handed me a few moments <orig reg="ago">a go</orig>.
                    how glad I was to hear from you. you must forgive me for not writing to you last
                        <orig reg="Thursday's">Thursdays</orig> mail it was on fault of mine I would
                    have written if my time had <orig reg="been">bin</orig> my own I <orig
                        reg="can't">cant</orig> write you but a few lines <orig reg="today">to
                    day</orig> I am quite well. I want to come down tomorrow week I will leave here
                    at Seven O clock I will reach Mt Solon <orig reg="about">a bout</orig> ten You
                    ask me if I love you I Do With all my heart <orig reg="there">thear</orig> is
                    nothing in this world that I love as well as you. I <orig reg="won't"
                    >wont</orig> sleep next time<pb n="2"/>but Stay <orig reg="awake">a wake</orig>
                    &amp; talk to you all the time Yes we will go down to Mossy Creek to church
                    if we <unclear>live</unclear> I must close</p>

                <p>My love to your Ma, love to all</p>

                <p>I love you I Send a kiss to you Good by</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours</salute>
                    <signed>David H Evans</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
